DIGEST
SB 305 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Edmonds
Proposed law (R.S. 17:3138.2) requires the Bd. of Regents to develop, maintain, and make
public a statewide dashboard that provides information on the alignment between
postsecondary degree programs and workforce outcomes in Louisiana.
Proposed law provides that the dashboard will be designed to assist students and their
families in understanding career outcomes associated with degree programs, policymakers
and state agencies in evaluating postsecondary program alignment with workforce needs,
and postsecondary institutions in strengthening program design and labor market relevance.
Proposed law provides that the dashboard include the following disaggregated information:
(1) Degree program completion data.
(2) Employment outcomes following completion, including industry and occupational
placement.
(3) Median and range of wages at defined intervals following completion.
